node.text:
On this Father's Day, we are honored to celebrate the life of @mikaelashiffrin’s late father Jeff, by announcing that the Jeff Shiffrin Athlete Resiliency Fund will live on as a newly established need-based, direct-to-athlete funding source for U.S. Ski & Snowboard athletes. 

We are deeply grateful to the Shiffrin family—Eileen, Taylor, and Mikaela—for their dedication and support in establishing this ongoing fund, for their commitment to athletes across all sports, and for their desire to honor Jeff’s legacy through this fund. 🤍

Learn more/donate at keeptheflamealive.org. (Link in bio)
#keeptheflamealive
#fathersday

node.text:
@jessiediggins is back with another core challenge!

Here it is:
1. Boat pose with right leg extended, left leg, then both legs
2. Leg lowers with weight held overhead - the farther back you hold it, the harder it gets!
3. Roll-ups that are slow and controlled, especially on the way down
4. Leg lowers at an angle to each side

Start with body weight, working your way up to holding a plate over your head - and if you’re feeling crazy, use a slosh tube (like @jessiediggins in the video) for the extra challenge of weight that unpredictably moves! Try 30 seconds of each exercise. 💪
